resource.title: Treatment plan for stroke
resource.description: Comprehensive treatment plan including Emergency care, Stroke rehabilitation

resource.conclusion: Patient shows improving status for stroke. Aisha Nguyen, a 56-year-old Asian female, presented with a severe stroke on 2021-03-05. She received emergency care including tPA administration and aspirin therapy. Subsequently, she underwent stroke rehabilitation with physical and occupational therapy, along with medication adjustments. Follow-up assessments show improving neurological function and rehabilitation progress.
